> @YaelDillies I rebased the commit to make git recognize this change as a rename. But the diff didn't change.

Doesn't matter how the commits are *within your PR*. What matters is how the commits are *across PRs*. You might have to split your PR into two/change the way you rename the files

Fortunately, another PR was in the process of merging this change as a split PR, so I cancelled it.
I will re-split this change tomorrow as it is already late today Japan time.
